{"pr_number": 2544, "pr_title": "[DOCS] Client Testing Guidelines", "pr_createdAt": "2020-12-14T10:33:43Z", "pr_url": "https://github.com/ls1intum/Artemis/pull/2544", "timeline": [{"oid": "2042abf5f0b6a0281b965c9bbd7c8159fc6d01c2", "url": "https://github.com/ls1intum/Artemis/commit/2042abf5f0b6a0281b965c9bbd7c8159fc6d01c2", "message": "Wrote some client testing guidelines", "committedDate": "2020-12-14T10:33:19Z", "type": "commit"}, {"oid": "4ef4aa16e8b968d3138f81afc323bed7690cbd6e", "url": "https://github.com/ls1intum/Artemis/commit/4ef4aa16e8b968d3138f81afc323bed7690cbd6e", "message": "Added sinon sandbox guideline", "committedDate": "2020-12-14T10:43:01Z", "type": "commit"}, {"oid": "ab35ffa8a82376d26e71d992864c3673451624a1", "url": "https://github.com/ls1intum/Artemis/commit/ab35ffa8a82376d26e71d992864c3673451624a1", "message": "Fix compiler warnings", "committedDate": "2020-12-14T15:34:44Z", "type": "commit"}, {"id": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDU0MjUzOTc4NA==", "url": "https://github.com/ls1intum/Artemis/pull/2544#discussion_r542539784", "bodyText": "We should imo add import { ComponentFixture, TestBed } from '@angular/core/testing'; to the import statements as we require ComponentFixture here and TestBed below.", "author": "FrankeLukas", "createdAt": "2020-12-14T16:50:56Z", "path": "docs/dev/guidelines/client.rst", "diffHunk": "@@ -90,4 +90,118 @@ Some general aspects:\n We use ``prettier`` to style code automatically and ``eslint`` to find additional issues.\n You can find the corresponding commands to invoked those tools in ``package.json``.\n \n+9. Testing\n+===========\n+\n+If you are new to client testing, it is highly recommended that you work through the testing part of the angular tutorial: https://angular.io/guide/testing.\n+\n+We use Jest (https://jestjs.io/) as our client testing framework.\n+\n+There are different tools available to support client testing. A common combination you can see in our codebase is:\n+\n+- Sinon (https://sinonjs.org/) for creating test spies, stubs and mocks\n+- Chai (https://www.chaijs.com/) with Sinon Chai (https://github.com/domenic/sinon-chai) for assertions.\n+- NgMocks (https://www.npmjs.com/package/ng-mocks) for mocking the dependencies of an angular component.\n+\n+The most basic test looks similar to this:\n+\n+ .. code:: ts\n+\n+    import * as chai from 'chai';\n+    import * as sinonChai from 'sinon-chai';\n+    import * as sinon from 'sinon';\n+\n+    chai.use(sinonChai);\n+    const expect = chai.expect;\n+\n+    describe('SomeComponent', () => {\n+        let someComponentFixture: ComponentFixture<SomeComponent>;", "originalCommit": "ab35ffa8a82376d26e71d992864c3673451624a1", "replyToReviewId": null, "replies": null, "type": "inlineReview"}, {"oid": "8ef8801be305abe89bd8761c506960c21cf11298", "url": "https://github.com/ls1intum/Artemis/commit/8ef8801be305abe89bd8761c506960c21cf11298", "message": "Modified docu", "committedDate": "2020-12-14T18:46:24Z", "type": "commit"}, {"oid": "07d091c2b5b4e77fcb6a466dbf0238c424c17296", "url": "https://github.com/ls1intum/Artemis/commit/07d091c2b5b4e77fcb6a466dbf0238c424c17296", "message": "Merge remote-tracking branch 'origin/doc/client-testing' into doc/client-testing", "committedDate": "2020-12-14T18:46:44Z", "type": "commit"}, {"oid": "1d214c7518757de5798fa832bfc6bb8580253553", "url": "https://github.com/ls1intum/Artemis/commit/1d214c7518757de5798fa832bfc6bb8580253553", "message": "Merge branch 'develop' into doc/client-testing", "committedDate": "2020-12-15T08:53:21Z", "type": "commit"}, {"oid": "af86c1f65db59b55462a5e06cb8d0f9f7c67d1ab", "url": "https://github.com/ls1intum/Artemis/commit/af86c1f65db59b55462a5e06cb8d0f9f7c67d1ab", "message": "Added section about using http mocks for more complicated services", "committedDate": "2020-12-15T09:49:38Z", "type": "commit"}, {"oid": "97c68b22840edf61aa57f5ba04eafe055434f468", "url": "https://github.com/ls1intum/Artemis/commit/97c68b22840edf61aa57f5ba04eafe055434f468", "mess